description:
Real-World Case Study of AI Org Change Management at Booking.com

We'll talk about the roadmap and lessons learned along the way to the following outcomes:

– the digital footprint across teams is LLM-Ready and fused with GenAI pipelines (e.g. Product Design, Engineering Design, Test Plans, Documentation, etc);

– everyone across teams (incl. PMs and EMs) uses a personal Local Agent for everyday work;

– a hierarchy of Agentic Skill Marketplaces mapped to domain knowledge and skills at appropriate organizational levels;

– coding is delegated to GenAI (spec-driven multi-agent) with proper guardrails and human-led validation.

Announcement draft: "Success in the GenAI Era is not about having few individuals who's masters in prompting, this doesn't scale. The crucial pillar here is a full team transformation, your entire team's processes, your entire SDLC has to evolve. This is a team sport, and it requires a collective shift in how you work."
